737
01:01:54,904 --> 01:01:58,084
I remember that moment I hit the switch.

738
01:01:58,968 --> 01:02:01,263
I did it because a Russian man told me

739
01:02:01,288 --> 01:02:05,133
that your power was coveted by
all the gifted who knew of it.

740
01:02:06,099 --> 01:02:09,170
The Russian's name was Fyodor.

741
01:02:09,343 --> 01:02:10,723
Exactly.

742
01:02:11,110 --> 01:02:13,356
That was the day you died.

743
01:02:14,204 --> 01:02:17,534
But after you died, your ability remained intact.

744
01:02:17,827 --> 01:02:22,091
Your ability didn't need your
body in order to continue its search.

745
01:02:22,477 --> 01:02:25,477
You had even forgotten your own death.

746
01:02:26,300 --> 01:02:30,481
But your ability made this room
to manage your growing collection.

747
01:02:32,042 --> 01:02:34,409
And now this is what you have become.

748
01:02:39,381 --> 01:02:41,808
That was the moment I used my claws.

749
01:02:42,248 --> 01:02:43,501
That's right.

750
01:02:43,788 --> 01:02:46,498
That was the moment when you killed me,

751
01:02:46,825 --> 01:02:48,626
using those claws.

752
01:02:48,657 --> 01:02:50,524
What do you expect me to do?!

753
01:02:50,663 --> 01:02:52,630
I didn't want to just die there!

754
01:02:52,655 --> 01:02:54,101
You pushed me too hard,

755
01:02:54,139 --> 01:02:57,121
I had to use the
tiger's claws to survive!

756
01:03:03,258 --> 01:03:05,385
It's the beginning of the end.

757
01:03:06,449 --> 01:03:07,202
Huh?

758
01:03:09,102 --> 01:03:12,403
Dazai, you're still here I see.

759
01:03:12,876 --> 01:03:17,166
Did you wish to witness this
city's demise from beyond the grave?

760
01:03:23,923 --> 01:03:26,010
In thanks to our new found friendship,

761
01:03:26,083 --> 01:03:29,130
I'll offer you a bite from the apple of knowledge.

762
01:03:29,920 --> 01:03:35,460
Even in the midst of the fog, my special
ability did not turn against me like the others.

763
01:03:35,705 --> 01:03:37,437
Do you know why that is?

764
01:03:46,701 --> 01:03:48,054
I am crime.

765
01:03:48,474 --> 01:03:49,968
I am punishment.

766
01:03:50,062 --> 01:03:51,663
Did you not know?

767
01:03:51,747 --> 01:03:54,542
Crime and punishment are close acquaintances.

768
01:03:54,913 --> 01:03:57,329
The borders that contain us vanish.

769
01:03:57,439 --> 01:03:59,172
And new rooms awaken.

770
01:04:00,955 --> 01:04:02,879
To the incarnation of death,

771
01:04:03,141 --> 01:04:05,794
the master of the ability-consuming fog...

772
01:04:06,048 --> 01:04:08,248
...obey your instinct to consume...

773
01:04:08,466 --> 01:04:10,776
Go on a rampage and roar!

774
01:04:11,840 --> 01:04:14,847
This isn't a singularity or loss of control.

775
01:04:18,025 --> 01:04:23,232
This is the dragon, the true form
of the chaos of special abilities.

776
01:04:32,719 --> 01:04:34,553
Anomaly readings are increasing.

777
01:04:34,619 --> 01:04:37,149
They're five times higher than they were six years ago.

778
01:04:37,222 --> 01:04:39,522
Make that five and half times higher and growing!

779
01:04:39,663 --> 01:04:41,961
What's the status of A5158?

780
01:04:42,876 --> 01:04:45,329
Try to keep your shit, would you?

781
01:04:52,545 --> 01:04:53,325
Chuuya...

782
01:04:53,705 --> 01:04:56,830
By now, it's likely Dazai has been eliminated.

783
01:04:56,913 --> 01:04:59,666
If you use your corrupted form, then you'll...

784
01:04:59,813 --> 01:05:01,553
I don't give a damn about that.

785
01:05:01,893 --> 01:05:03,293
Why would you say that?

786
01:05:03,621 --> 01:05:07,420
Then you won't be able to take my
life as your reward for doing the job.

787
01:05:08,087 --> 01:05:10,080
Don't get cocky, asshole.

788
01:05:11,279 --> 01:05:14,851
You were just a lowly infiltrator six years ago.

789
01:05:14,955 --> 01:05:19,099
Nobody listened to you when you said
it was a mistake to hire Shibusawa.

790
01:05:20,102 --> 01:05:22,398
He's the one who screwed things up.

791
01:05:23,019 --> 01:05:26,619
That idiot Dazai is still alive in that tower...

792
01:05:27,169 --> 01:05:28,109
I'm sure of it.

793
01:05:28,702 --> 01:05:30,689
I'm gonna go give him a good smack.

794
01:05:31,389 --> 01:05:32,522
I'm hanging up.

795
01:05:36,513 --> 01:05:37,839
I'm counting on you.

796
01:05:41,329 --> 01:05:42,803
We're approaching the target.

797
01:05:45,629 --> 01:05:47,763
Aren't you the chick I saw a while back?

798
01:05:47,788 --> 01:05:48,894
I'm Tsujimura.

799
01:05:49,872 --> 01:05:51,661
Do you really intend to do this?

800
01:05:52,251 --> 01:05:53,038
Yeah.

801
01:05:53,121 --> 01:05:54,327
It'll never work.

802
01:05:55,001 --> 01:05:56,567
You're not in the same league!

803
01:05:56,741 --> 01:05:59,574
That monster is beyond human comprehension.

804
01:06:00,121 --> 01:06:01,277
Try to fight it,

805
01:06:01,824 --> 01:06:03,317
and you're gonna die.

806
01:06:04,163 --> 01:06:08,373
You're gonna have to give me a better
reason than that to chicken out and go home.

807
01:06:10,463 --> 01:06:13,574
Do you know when it's okay to chicken out and go home?

808
01:06:17,671 --> 01:06:18,605
No, I don't.

809
01:06:19,798 --> 01:06:22,511
Well, the answer's never.

810
01:06:28,030 --> 01:06:30,904
Grantors of dark disgrace...

811
01:06:34,614 --> 01:06:36,194
You need not...

812
01:06:36,496 --> 01:06:38,939
You need not wake me again!

813
01:06:58,147 --> 01:06:59,615
The readings are all rising.

814
01:06:59,640 --> 01:07:00,709
What's happening?

815
01:07:00,920 --> 01:07:03,356
His special ability
is gravity control.

816
01:07:04,580 --> 01:07:05,256
However,

817
01:07:05,705 --> 01:07:10,103
in his current state of Corruption,
he's not lucid enough to control that power.

818
01:07:10,413 --> 01:07:12,189
And neither can he disable it.

819
01:07:12,343 --> 01:07:15,069
Are you saying the only way
to stop it is for him to die?

820
01:07:15,246 --> 01:07:19,874
We only know of one other method that
works and that's Dazai's nullification ability.

821
01:07:20,194 --> 01:07:21,074
Without that...

822
01:07:21,496 --> 01:07:22,866
There's no hope for him.

823
01:07:22,966 --> 01:07:23,732
No...

824
01:08:35,163 --> 01:08:43,287
Dazai!!!

825
01:09:35,091 --> 01:09:38,477
You used Corruption, believing that I would save you?

826
01:09:38,737 --> 01:09:40,064
How beautiful.

827
01:09:40,557 --> 01:09:47,802
What I believed in, was your disgusting
craftiness and stubborn refusal to ever die.

828
01:09:48,131 --> 01:09:49,504
A small critique,

829
01:09:49,617 --> 01:09:52,991
that was a rather violent way to wake up Snow White.

830
01:09:53,117 --> 01:09:56,782
Snow White never hid a poison antidote in her mouth.

831
01:09:57,455 --> 01:09:59,495
You knew I was gonna punch you.

832
01:10:03,552 --> 01:10:05,565
Let go off me, asshole.

833
01:10:05,605 --> 01:10:06,512
Stay still.

834
01:10:06,817 --> 01:10:07,810
Why?

835
01:10:07,943 --> 01:10:10,457
The fog hasn't
lifted from this area.

836
01:10:10,590 --> 01:10:15,933
I'd rather not have to protect you against
your own special ability at this very moment.

837
01:10:16,127 --> 01:10:18,167
It's still not over?

838
01:10:18,500 --> 01:10:19,627
Afraid not...

839
01:10:19,800 --> 01:10:21,377
It's just beginning.

840
01:10:21,884 --> 01:10:23,490
Dammit.

841
01:10:23,557 --> 01:10:26,149
Well I'm not going
anywhere right now.

842
01:10:26,409 --> 01:10:28,429
I think I'm gonna pass out.

843
01:10:30,371 --> 01:10:32,536
I was able to predict this much.

844
01:10:33,146 --> 01:10:34,180
But now...

845
01:10:34,526 --> 01:10:36,400
The rest is all on them.

846
01:10:38,969 --> 01:10:41,022
You acted as though you knew everything,

847
01:10:41,069 --> 01:10:43,215
when the reality was quite the opposite.

848
01:10:43,609 --> 01:10:48,272
This fog will continue to spread
until Earth becomes a dead apple.

849
01:10:48,512 --> 01:10:51,446
The entire planet will be a fruit of death.

850
01:10:52,086 --> 01:10:54,711
I have a small gift I'd like to impart to you.

851
01:10:55,771 --> 01:10:58,921
It's a fragment of the crystal that gathers abilities.

852
01:11:00,468 --> 01:11:04,095
Using this, you are the singularity.

853
01:11:12,621 --> 01:11:15,354
I remember everything, now.

854
01:11:16,081 --> 01:11:20,598
What I was seeking wasn't a special
ability to transcend all others.

855
01:11:20,758 --> 01:11:26,705
It was the glimmer of light of a tenacious life
force that would prevail over my special ability.

856
01:11:26,783 --> 01:11:29,143
It was stronger than my own fate.

857
01:11:29,830 --> 01:11:31,263
By killing me,

858
01:11:31,443 --> 01:11:35,033
your soul had demonstrated for me the power of life.

859
01:11:35,600 --> 01:11:38,456
Show me your light once more!

860
01:12:13,448 --> 01:12:15,155
The fog has begun to spread again!

861
01:12:15,652 --> 01:12:17,982
The singularity variance is immeasurable.

862
01:12:18,132 --> 01:12:21,003
It's expanding at 120 kilometers per hour.

863
01:12:21,277 --> 01:12:25,657
At this rate, the whole Kanto region
will be engulfed in one hour and 35 minutes.

864
01:12:26,079 --> 01:12:29,334
In 12 hours and 36 minutes, it will be all of Tokyo,

865
01:12:29,580 --> 01:12:32,685
and in 168 hours, the entire planet!

866
01:12:34,117 --> 01:12:35,391
Are you serious?

867
01:12:35,769 --> 01:12:36,422
Wait...

868
01:12:36,621 --> 01:12:40,411
We have an incoming call from the
English special operations organization.

869
01:12:40,997 --> 01:12:43,850
It's... from the Order of the Clock Tower.

870
01:12:46,104 --> 01:12:47,817
A good day to you all.

871
01:12:48,663 --> 01:12:50,621
On behalf of the nations of Europe,

872
01:12:50,755 --> 01:12:54,135
our hearts go out to your country in this time of need.

873
01:12:54,609 --> 01:12:59,804
On that note however, in order to prevent this
crisis from spreading to the rest of the world,

874
01:13:00,079 --> 01:13:03,787
we have deployed a gifted agent
with an incineration ability.

875
01:13:08,475 --> 01:13:10,204
An incineration ability...?!

876
01:13:10,877 --> 01:13:12,031
When does he arrive?

877
01:13:12,564 --> 01:13:16,294
Exactly 30 minutes; at the very crack of dawn.

878
01:13:18,698 --> 01:13:21,572
They're going to burn Yokohama to the ground.

879
01:13:26,362 --> 01:13:28,715
I've found you, Shibusawa.

880
01:13:29,129 --> 01:13:30,749
Rashoumon!

881
01:13:33,661 --> 01:13:34,921
Demonic...

882
01:13:37,589 --> 01:13:38,752
...Armor!

883
01:13:43,740 --> 01:13:44,613
Ho ho...

884
01:13:45,147 --> 01:13:47,353
You two are gifted, I assume?

885
01:13:47,993 --> 01:13:49,776
What's he mean "you two"?

886
01:13:52,043 --> 01:13:53,376
Why are you here?

887
01:13:53,749 --> 01:13:54,773
It's very simple.

888
01:13:54,973 --> 01:13:57,747
I just want Atsushi to continue to live in the light.

889
01:13:58,507 --> 01:14:01,017
So I'll be the one who kills this man.

890
01:14:01,383 --> 01:14:02,830
Come, Demon Snow!

891
01:14:10,236 --> 01:14:15,519
How remarkable that two gifteds were
able to take back their special abilities.

892
01:14:15,790 --> 01:14:17,870
We have taken
our abilities back.

893
01:14:18,079 --> 01:14:20,010
And we won't be
the only ones who do!

894
01:14:23,633 --> 01:14:27,980
I expect this, too, was within
your calculations, wasn't it, Dazai?

895
01:14:28,517 --> 01:14:29,330
Oh...

896
01:14:29,637 --> 01:14:32,404
Looks like I have my own guest to entertain.

897
01:14:35,567 --> 01:14:38,233
Rintarou... I love you!

898
01:14:42,344 --> 01:14:44,604
My adorable, dear Elise.

899
01:14:44,997 --> 01:14:47,330
I can't bring myself to slice you up.

900
01:14:47,930 --> 01:14:48,966
Dear me...

901
01:14:49,229 --> 01:14:51,286
What is the optimal solution here?

902
01:14:56,161 --> 01:14:58,761
It's logical your swordsmanship would equal mine.

903
01:14:59,038 --> 01:15:00,708
Our skills may be matched,

904
01:15:00,913 --> 01:15:04,225
but you're far too conservative to gain the upper hand.

905
01:15:04,561 --> 01:15:07,294
Without a devious nature to your strikes,

906
01:15:07,408 --> 01:15:09,851
you have no hope of winning against me.

907
01:15:12,165 --> 01:15:14,271
That you, Master Fukuzawa?

908
01:15:17,507 --> 01:15:18,627
Mr. Mori.

909
01:15:18,700 --> 01:15:20,154
What a coincidence.

910
01:15:20,220 --> 01:15:22,323
Encountering some difficulties?

911
01:15:22,717 --> 01:15:25,135
I think I may have a solution to our problem,

912
01:15:25,415 --> 01:15:27,051
how to bring this to an end.

913
01:15:27,537 --> 01:15:29,207
What excellent news.

914
01:15:29,371 --> 01:15:31,663
When you think of everything we've done till now,

915
01:15:31,747 --> 01:15:35,691
doesn't it seem like our actions
were merely a rehearsal for this moment?

916
01:15:47,031 --> 01:15:49,604
I thought you only used your scalpel.

917
01:15:50,891 --> 01:15:52,671
I'll be mindful of that.

918
01:15:53,288 --> 01:15:56,684
Yet it's the Silver Wolf who showed a sweet girl no mercy.

919
01:15:56,831 --> 01:16:00,290
The way I see it. You're the one to watch out for.

920
01:16:00,468 --> 01:16:02,454
That thing was nothing but a fiend.

921
01:16:03,163 --> 01:16:05,706
Heyyyyy, Rintarouuuu!

922
01:16:06,066 --> 01:16:09,099
Just what the heck were you
thinking, leaving me behiiiind?!

923
01:16:09,166 --> 01:16:11,809
It's so nice to see the real Elise.

924
01:16:11,889 --> 01:16:14,669
Still a fiend, as far as I'm concerned.

925
01:16:21,801 --> 01:16:24,375
Is there even a spark left to my life?

926
01:16:25,368 --> 01:16:28,630
No matter where I look, I can't seem to find it.

927
01:16:29,413 --> 01:16:31,550
When the fog took away my ability,

928
01:16:31,723 --> 01:16:33,436
I was honestly relieved.

929
01:16:34,410 --> 01:16:36,447
Now that we were two separate beings,

930
01:16:37,020 --> 01:16:38,820
I wouldn't have to hurt anyone again.

931
01:16:43,937 --> 01:16:45,324
But then I remembered,

932
01:16:45,837 --> 01:16:48,230
that the tiger actually saved me once.

933
01:16:56,251 --> 01:16:59,731
I've been consumed by the
jaws of death once before.

934
01:16:59,830 --> 01:17:03,281
How do you expect to kill
something that is already dead?!

935
01:17:03,846 --> 01:17:05,333
You abomination!

936
01:17:10,121 --> 01:17:13,498
No matter much I run, the tiger still follows.

937
01:17:16,735 --> 01:17:17,584
Huh?

938
01:17:18,978 --> 01:17:22,295
I might as well be trying to
escape the beating of my own heart.

939
01:17:23,402 --> 01:17:27,799
This whole time, you've been
the strength I've used to stay alive.

940
01:17:33,225 --> 01:17:36,162
I can hear you more clearly than ever now.

941
01:17:37,121 --> 01:17:38,889
I understand you now.

942
01:17:42,455 --> 01:17:43,952
And I can feel...

943
01:17:44,913 --> 01:17:47,746
the fire in everyone's spirit.

944
01:17:53,429 --> 01:17:55,580
I expect the same from you.

945
01:17:57,740 --> 01:18:00,193
If you don't keep up, I'll leave you behind.

946
01:18:01,038 --> 01:18:03,350
Tiger! Let's get out there!

947
01:18:13,621 --> 01:18:14,936
Look at your faces.

948
01:18:15,121 --> 01:18:17,483
I have taken your last spark of hope.

949
01:18:17,788 --> 01:18:18,784
However...

950
01:18:18,883 --> 01:18:21,613
I want so much more than that!

951
01:18:23,540 --> 01:18:24,193
Huh?

952
01:18:30,361 --> 01:18:33,041
The dragon and the tiger deserve each other.

953
01:18:36,204 --> 01:18:40,405
The Russian who told me of your
existence also told me about the dragon,

954
01:18:40,712 --> 01:18:45,162
and how it is the true form of
the chaos of special abilities.

955
01:18:47,231 --> 01:18:48,104
Therefore,

956
01:18:48,634 --> 01:18:53,404
when you embody the tiger, you become
the antithesis of all special abilities.

957
01:18:53,429 --> 01:18:54,288
Finally.

958
01:18:54,764 --> 01:18:55,814
Took you long enough.

959
01:18:56,274 --> 01:18:58,955
So tell me, Atsushi Nakajima,

960
01:18:59,121 --> 01:19:00,885
plan to kill me again?

961
01:19:02,995 --> 01:19:06,972
I'm only here to put a certain
thing back where it already belongs.

962
01:19:07,014 --> 01:19:08,781
Then you should understand,

963
01:19:09,205 --> 01:19:10,871
I won't stop you!

964
01:19:13,959 --> 01:19:15,795
Very good!

965
01:19:16,162 --> 01:19:19,463
But then, you are quite special indeed!

966
01:19:22,705 --> 01:19:27,054
You have single-handedly cured my boredom!

967
01:19:48,556 --> 01:19:49,790
Demon Snow!

968
01:19:57,056 --> 01:19:58,876
This city is where we belong,

969
01:19:59,163 --> 01:20:01,796
and the three of us have to work together to protect it.

970
01:20:03,066 --> 01:20:03,760
Huh?

971
01:20:05,753 --> 01:20:07,080
It's up to us.

972
01:20:07,121 --> 01:20:08,834
Can you call Demon Snow again?

973
01:20:11,275 --> 01:20:13,622
Both of you, listen to me.

974
01:20:14,913 --> 01:20:16,663
If we're gonna bring him down,

975
01:20:16,782 --> 01:20:18,738
you know what we need to do, right?

976
01:20:19,572 --> 01:20:21,385
Yeah... I do.

977
01:20:23,163 --> 01:20:23,905
Kyouka...

978
01:20:26,705 --> 01:20:29,822
Earlier, you told me you couldn't hate Demon Snow.

979
01:20:30,522 --> 01:20:32,251
I know she'll respond to you.

980
01:20:47,830 --> 01:20:50,674
Your naivete is so beautiful.

981
01:20:52,830 --> 01:20:53,820
Now, Kyouka!

982
01:20:54,547 --> 01:20:56,914
Demon Snow, defeat my enemy!

983
01:21:04,282 --> 01:21:06,948
You can't think this is enough to stop me!

984
01:21:08,830 --> 01:21:10,203
Your turn, Akutagawa!

985
01:21:10,228 --> 01:21:12,054
As if I need your permission!

986
01:21:19,211 --> 01:21:20,784
You won't get away this time.

987
01:21:27,368 --> 01:21:28,604
This is it...

988
01:21:29,029 --> 01:21:30,849
This is it!

989
01:21:31,311 --> 01:21:34,854
The ecstasy of feeling my death.

990
01:21:36,394 --> 01:21:38,124
Do you wish to feel it, too?!

991
01:21:42,011 --> 01:21:42,965
What's happening?

992
01:21:50,422 --> 01:21:53,442
Show me once more that glimmer of light,

993
01:21:53,636 --> 01:21:56,469
the one that can oppose all gifted powers!

994
01:22:08,139 --> 01:22:09,306
Beautiful...

995
01:22:10,182 --> 01:22:13,642
This is indeed the pinnacle
of special abilities!

996
01:22:14,016 --> 01:22:14,825
Wrong!

997
01:22:16,705 --> 01:22:17,452
What?!

998
01:22:18,552 --> 01:22:20,527
It's much more than an ability.

999
01:22:21,273 --> 01:22:24,420
That thing is me!

1000
01:22:49,663 --> 01:22:50,485
Yes.

1001
01:22:50,944 --> 01:22:53,317
Now I understand everything.

1002
01:22:54,417 --> 01:22:56,271
The answer to why I'm here,

1003
01:22:56,697 --> 01:22:59,472
the purpose of you appearing before me,

1004
01:22:59,631 --> 01:23:01,712
and the meaning of that man's words,

1005
01:23:02,172 --> 01:23:04,589
I understand all of it now.

1006
01:23:06,129 --> 01:23:07,155
It's you.

1007
01:23:08,449 --> 01:23:12,192
You must be the angel who has come just to save me.

1008
01:24:08,101 --> 01:24:08,810
Hmm...

1009
01:24:10,969 --> 01:24:11,730
Huh?

1010
01:24:30,443 --> 01:24:34,190
Sir, both the singularity and the fog have disappeared.

1011
01:24:39,752 --> 01:24:43,465
The Order of the Clock Tower has informed
us that they have aborted their mission.

1012
01:24:47,034 --> 01:24:48,294
What a shame.

1013
01:24:48,888 --> 01:24:53,221
The scent of a burning nation
would've gone well with my tea.

1014
01:24:56,731 --> 01:24:58,917
What the hell are you doing here?

1015
01:24:59,560 --> 01:25:02,350
Dazai's fine if that's who you were looking for.

1016
01:25:09,707 --> 01:25:10,487
Hey...

1017
01:25:13,034 --> 01:25:14,440
Help me with my hat?

1018
01:25:17,961 --> 01:25:21,242
Well, I'm not a gifted, and I ended up back here fine.

1019
01:25:21,316 --> 01:25:23,682
So things must have worked out well in the end.

1020
01:25:24,009 --> 01:25:26,909
It seems Atsushi's become pretty competent.

1021
01:25:27,242 --> 01:25:28,819
Wouldn't you agree, Dazai?

1022
01:25:42,722 --> 01:25:46,055
Atsushi, about what I was doing earlier...

1023
01:25:46,408 --> 01:25:47,808
What you were doing...?

1024
01:25:48,602 --> 01:25:52,045
I know that everything you did was to protect this city.

1025
01:25:53,305 --> 01:25:56,795
Do I really look like someone
who's overflowing with virtue to you?

1026
01:25:57,689 --> 01:25:59,395
Uh, yeah, you do.

1027
01:26:01,269 --> 01:26:03,032
Well, if ya say so.

1028
01:26:08,830 --> 01:26:13,666
I hope he was able to find the escape from
loneliness and boredom he was searching for.

1029
01:26:15,345 --> 01:26:17,958
Is that the same thing you've been searching for?

1030
01:26:20,329 --> 01:26:23,668
If it was possible for Shibusawa
to forget he'd been killed,

1031
01:26:24,155 --> 01:26:27,682
I'm pretty sure Dazai can forget
about his own past one more time.

1032
01:26:29,105 --> 01:26:30,625
But this much is true.

1033
01:26:31,158 --> 01:26:32,872
We protected this city,

1034
01:26:32,972 --> 01:26:35,963
and I'm so proud that we were able to do it together.

1035
01:26:36,623 --> 01:26:39,769
I think the world is a little
more beautiful now because of that.

1036
01:26:40,621 --> 01:26:43,140
And because I have all of you in my life.

1037
01:26:53,580 --> 01:26:54,876
Heyyy!

1038
01:26:57,723 --> 01:27:00,444
I see you blockheads are all still alive!

1039
01:27:00,830 --> 01:27:02,464
They made it out safe too!

1040
01:27:02,918 --> 01:27:04,058
Of course they did.

1041
01:27:04,518 --> 01:27:06,961
We are the Armed Detective Agency...

1042
01:27:08,570 --> 01:27:09,363
...aren't we?

1043
01:27:12,127 --> 01:27:13,120
Yeah.

1044
01:27:21,277 --> 01:27:25,554
It's a miracle that after everything that
happened, there were no civilian casualties.

1045
01:27:25,821 --> 01:27:27,787
We were really quite lucky.

1046
01:27:30,547 --> 01:27:33,371
I know we've been working non-stop for days now,

1047
01:27:33,591 --> 01:27:35,884
but we need to keep at it, Tsujimura.

1048
01:27:36,098 --> 01:27:39,656
It's hopeless! We'll never cover all of this up!

1049
01:27:40,204 --> 01:27:45,290
Even though the damage was confined to a
small zone in Yokohama, it was pretty extensive.

1050
01:27:47,428 --> 01:27:48,447
Hey, boss...

1051
01:27:48,538 --> 01:27:49,033
Hm?

1052
01:27:50,073 --> 01:27:52,747
I still don't understand exactly what happened.

1053
01:27:52,830 --> 01:27:54,116
Can you explain it?

1054
01:27:54,788 --> 01:27:56,229
I don't know myself.

1055
01:27:56,717 --> 01:28:00,830
Given the complexity of the three individuals
who were at the center of the conflict,

1056
01:28:00,855 --> 01:28:02,580
we may never get a full picture.

1057
01:28:04,222 --> 01:28:06,304
Dazai's always been enigmatic,

1058
01:28:06,329 --> 01:28:10,096
and the motives of that demon
Fyodor are impossible to fathom.

1059
01:28:10,778 --> 01:28:11,547
Still...

1060
01:28:12,600 --> 01:28:15,580
Let's assume those two told each other nothing but lies.

1061
01:28:15,954 --> 01:28:19,131
Then the fundamental truth might be deceptively simple.

1062
01:28:19,898 --> 01:28:20,498
Huh?

1063
01:28:21,788 --> 01:28:25,142
Shibusawa possessed an unnatural degree of intelligence.

1064
01:28:26,344 --> 01:28:28,260
He couldn't understand other people.

1065
01:28:28,647 --> 01:28:29,754
He could use them.

1066
01:28:30,114 --> 01:28:31,020
Destroy them.

1067
01:28:31,374 --> 01:28:33,664
Or he might have even wanted to save them.

1068
01:28:34,384 --> 01:28:37,464
Actually all three of them seem much like aliens.

1069
01:28:37,747 --> 01:28:39,941
Lonely and isolated in the world.

1070
01:28:40,914 --> 01:28:43,441
I'm not sure I would be able to live like that!

1071
01:28:44,079 --> 01:28:44,747
Uh...

1072
01:28:44,830 --> 01:28:46,445
Miss... Tsujimura?

1073
01:28:48,705 --> 01:28:51,940
You knew he'd have a trick up
his sleeve, didn't you, boss?

1074
01:28:52,315 --> 01:28:55,454
Well, with Dazai acting on his own,

1075
01:28:55,830 --> 01:28:58,028
I expected he would need your help.

1076
01:28:58,560 --> 01:29:00,741
To set the stage, so to speak.

1077
01:29:00,840 --> 01:29:02,871
So I was just the opening act?

1078
01:29:03,038 --> 01:29:06,580
You know full well that Dazai decides the star.

1079
01:29:06,830 --> 01:29:09,557
So, what's my payment then?

1080
01:29:10,243 --> 01:29:12,497
The return of order to this city.

1081
01:29:13,457 --> 01:29:15,837
I get life-long bragging rights?

1082
01:29:16,038 --> 01:29:17,477
I guess I can live with that.

1083
01:29:17,884 --> 01:29:19,645
Excellent job, Chuuya.

1084
01:29:20,085 --> 01:29:22,429
Nah, you don't have to commend me.

1085
01:29:22,685 --> 01:29:23,842
It was your order.

1086
01:29:24,038 --> 01:29:25,994
I was just doing my job.

1087
01:29:27,521 --> 01:29:29,717
Everything is just entertainment.

1088
01:29:30,254 --> 01:29:34,246
However, this world, so rife with crime and punishment,

1089
01:29:34,717 --> 01:29:38,487
and in order to finally end it, I do need that novel.

1090
01:29:39,538 --> 01:29:43,081
A special book that sleeps somewhere within this city.

1091
01:29:44,364 --> 01:29:46,589
And lastly, do not insult our clients!

1092
01:29:46,621 --> 01:29:47,887
Is that understood?

1093
01:29:47,967 --> 01:29:51,545
You really are like the Agency's
mommy, aren't you, Kunikida?

1094
01:29:51,767 --> 01:29:52,692
Mommy?!

1095
01:29:54,246 --> 01:29:56,832
Hey! Don't work too hard out there, you two!

1096
01:29:56,955 --> 01:29:57,788
Off you go then.

1097
01:29:58,188 --> 01:29:59,468
Take care, okay!

1098
01:29:59,942 --> 01:30:02,322
We will. See ya later, guys!

